Real Madrid has confirmed that the club has reached an agreement with Inter Milan over the transfer of right-back, Achraf Hakimi. The Los Blancos made the announcement in a statement via its official website on Thursday. It said: “Real Madrid Football Club and Inter Milan have reached an agreement over the transfer of Achraf Hakimi. “The club wishes to thank Achraf for his many years of dedication, professionalism and exemplary conduct since he joined our academy in 2006 and wishes him all the very best in this new chapter.” DAILY POST recalls that Hakimi had drawn the interest of Inter Milan in the past few weeks. The 21-year-old Morocco international spent the 2019/20 season on loan at Borussia Dortmund from Real Madrid.